5/5
These are just some of the reasons why I prefer to go out earlier than usual whenever I'm travelling. This blue-hour shot of the Singapore skyline is still available on @opensea. You can check out my Singapore collection at https://t.co/MJ702BbDO5. https://t.co/EEbU2wC97p

4/5 
The early morning air is good for one's health. Filling your lungs with the cool morning air can greatly enhance your mood.

3/5
Fewer people means you can easily focus on your craft. I personally find it hard to shoot, whenever I know that somebody is watching me.

2/5 
As with any prime tourist destination, you can expect a lot of tourists in major landmarks. As somebody who requires a tripod and a space, this is basically a challenge. Going out early means there are less tourists.

1/5
